<h1>Actress Virginia Mayo dies</h1>
&lt;strong class="published"&gt;&lt;span id="publishDate" class="value-title" title=""&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span class="Z3988" style="display:none" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rfr_id=rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:User%3ADendodge&amp;rft_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:&amp;rft.atitle=Actress%20Virginia%20Mayo%20dies&amp;rft.jtitle=Wikinews&amp;rft.date=&amp;rft.aucorp=Wikinews+contributors&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.rights=CC-BY+2.5&amp;rft.identifier=&amp;rft.artnum="&gt; &lt;/span&gt; 
&lt;a href="w%3AVirginia%20Mayo"&gt;Virginia Mayo&lt;/a&gt;, an actress famous for her movie roles of the 1940s and 1950s, died Monday, &lt;a href="w%3AJanuary%2017"&gt;January 17&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="w%3A2005"&gt;2005&lt;/a&gt; in a nursing home in Thousand Oaks, California, of pneumonia and heart failure.

