<h1>News Briefs: January 28, 2005</h1>
&lt;strong class="published"&gt;&lt;span id="publishDate" class="value-title" title=""&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span class="Z3988" style="display:none" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rfr_id=rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:User%3ADendodge&amp;rft_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:&amp;rft.atitle=News%20Briefs%3A%20January%2028%2C%202005&amp;rft.jtitle=Wikinews&amp;rft.date=&amp;rft.aucorp=Wikinews+contributors&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.rights=CC-BY+2.5&amp;rft.identifier=&amp;rft.artnum="&gt; &lt;/span&gt; 

♡❤Wikinews Staff Reports♡❤ – The following stories made international headlines today:

<h3>&lt;a href="w%3AInternational%20Space%20Station"&gt;International Space Station&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="w%3AAstronaut"&gt;crew&lt;/a&gt; take 5.5 hour &lt;a href="w%3AExtra-vehicular%20activity"&gt;spacewalk&lt;/a&gt;</h3>

&lt;a href="w%3ARussia"&gt;Russian&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="w%3ASalizhan%20Shakirovich%20Sharipov"&gt;Salizhan Sharipov&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="w%3AUnited%20States"&gt;U.S.&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="w%3ALeroy%20Chiao"&gt;w:Leroy Chiao&lt;/a&gt; installed equipment on the exterior of the ISS, including the 20-inch robotic arm. They also inspected and photographed the oxygen generator and carbondioxide scrubber, which have had mechanical issues, and discovered an unexpected patch of oily brownish-black residue near the vents.


