<doc id="4242" url="https://en.wikinews.org/wiki?curid=4242" title="Production of GM soy crops surges in Romania">
<h1>Production of GM soy crops surges in Romania</h1>
&lt;strong class="published"&gt;&lt;span id="publishDate" class="value-title" title=""&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span class="Z3988" style="display:none" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rfr_id=rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:User%3ADendodge&amp;rft_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:&amp;rft.atitle=Production%20of%20GM%20soy%20crops%20surges%20in%20Romania&amp;rft.jtitle=Wikinews&amp;rft.date=&amp;rft.aucorp=Wikinews+contributors&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.rights=CC-BY+2.5&amp;rft.identifier=&amp;rft.artnum="&gt; &lt;/span&gt; 

&lt;a href="w%3ABucharest"&gt;BUCHAREST&lt;/a&gt;, Romania – The average production of &lt;a href="%3Aw%3Agenetically-modified"&gt;genetically-modified&lt;/a&gt; (GM) &lt;a href="%3Aw%3Asoybean"&gt;soy&lt;/a&gt; grew by 50 tonnes to 250 tonnes per square kilometre last year, said Constantin Sin from the Romanian Ministry of Agriculture. Soy is the only GM crop allowed in &lt;a href="%3Aw%3ARomania"&gt;Romania&lt;/a&gt; for commercial purposes. Additionally, the area cultivated with the modified soy increased from 396 km² in 2003 to 581 km² in 2004. GM soy is mainly farmed in southeastern Romania, in the counties of &lt;a href="%3Aw%3ABraila%20%28county%29"&gt;Brăila&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="%3Aw%3ACalarasi%20%28county%29"&gt;Călăraşi&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="%3Aw%3AIalomita"&gt;Ialomiţa&lt;/a&gt;.

In 1996, the &lt;a href="%3Aw%3AEuropean%20Union"&gt;European Union&lt;/a&gt; endorsed the import of transgenic soy, and, in 2004, the green light was given for the sale of new genetically-modified products which were used for animal breeding. Globally, the largest producers of genetically-modified soy are the &lt;a href="%3Aw%3AUnited%20States%20of%20America"&gt;United States of America&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="%3Aw%3AArgentina"&gt;Argentina&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="%3Aw%3ABrazil"&gt;Brazil&lt;/a&gt;.

