<doc id="4484" url="https://en.wikinews.org/wiki?curid=4484" title="The Aviator and Vera Drake scoop top prizes at the 2005 Orange BAFTA Film Awards">
<h1>The Aviator and Vera Drake scoop top prizes at the 2005 Orange BAFTA Film Awards</h1>
&lt;strong class="published"&gt;&lt;span id="publishDate" class="value-title" title=""&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span class="Z3988" style="display:none" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rfr_id=rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:User%3ADendodge&amp;rft_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:&amp;rft.atitle=The%20Aviator%20and%20Vera%20Drake%20scoop%20top%20prizes%20at%20the%202005%20Orange%20BAFTA%20Film%20Awards&amp;rft.jtitle=Wikinews&amp;rft.date=&amp;rft.aucorp=Wikinews+contributors&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.rights=CC-BY+2.5&amp;rft.identifier=&amp;rft.artnum="&gt; &lt;/span&gt; 
LONDON – The big-budget Hollywood movie ♡❤&lt;a href="w%3AThe%20Aviator"&gt;The Aviator&lt;/a&gt;♡❤ and the low-budget Brit flick ♡❤&lt;a href="w%3AVera%20Drake"&gt;Vera Drake&lt;/a&gt;♡❤ have scooped the main prizes at the 2005 Orange BAFTA Film Awards. Four gongs went to The Aviator with the top ones being Best Film and &lt;a href="w%3ACate%20Blanchett"&gt;Cate Blanchett&lt;/a&gt; for Best Supporting Actress. Vera Drake got three gongs with Best Director, Best Actress &amp; Costume Design. &lt;a href="Jamie%20Foxx"&gt;Jamie Foxx&lt;/a&gt; got Best Actor with &lt;a href="w%3ARay"&gt;Ray&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="w%3AClive%20Owen"&gt;Clive Owen&lt;/a&gt; got Best Supporting Actor with &lt;a href="w%3ACloser"&gt;Closer&lt;/a&gt;.

